comments.body: I haven't messed with any of those three genera at all yet and finally just threw them up hoping for some help. Thanks Dave!

I have never seen an SWG with such a well-defined and beautiful ST line. I do think this is Euacidalia, but which one. In my own classification system for the SWGs, based on the few MPG images and a few from BOLD (which may or may not be right) I identify the light brown specimens as brownsvillea and the light gray ones as sericearia. This one is sort of inbetween, but with that gorgeous ST line, I would identify it as sericearia.
The white vertex would be a character of Euacidalia, Protoproutia, or Eumacrodes. If I've got it right, them the white dorsal stripe like seen here is usually seen on Euacidalia.
